variables.name: profileFd
variables.comment: File descriptor for profile output file, can be null.

variables.name: samplingInterval
variables.comment: Indicates sample profiling when nonzero, interval in microseconds.

variables.name: autoStopProfiler
variables.comment: Automatically stop the profiler when the app goes idle.

variables.name: streamingOutput
variables.comment: * Indicates whether to stream the profiling info to the out file continuously.

variables.name: agent
variables.comment: * Denotes an agent (and its parameters) to attach for profiling.

variables.name: attachAgentDuringBind
variables.comment:
* Whether the {@link agent} should be attached early (before bind-application) or during
     * bind-application. Agents attached prior to binding cannot be loaded from the app's APK
     * directly and must be given as an absolute path (or available in the default LD_LIBRARY_PATH).
     * Agents attached during bind-application will miss early setup (e.g., resource initialization
     * and classloader generation), but are searched in the app's library search path.

methods.name: public ProfilerInfo setAgent(String agent, boolean attachAgentDuringBind)
methods.comment:
* Return a new ProfilerInfo instance, with fields populated from this object,
     * and {@link agent} and {@link attachAgentDuringBind} as given.

methods.name: public void closeFd()
methods.comment: * Close profileFd, if it is open. The field will be null after a call to this function.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(Parcel out, int flags)
public void dumpDebug(ProtoOutputStream proto, long fieldId)
